inisters of the United Kingdom}}\n{{Great Offices of State}}\n{{Ministers at HM Treasury}}\n{{Leaders of political parties in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Johnson Cabinet}}\n{{Current G8 Leaders}}\n{{G20 Leaders}}\n{{NATO leaders}}\n{{European Council}}\n{{Current heads of government in the UK and dependencies}}\n{{Commonwealth Chairpersons-in-Office}}\n{{Mayors of London}}\n{{Foreign Secretary}}\n{{First May Cabinet}}\n{{Second May Cabinet}}\n{{Conservative Party (UK)}}\n{{Conservative Party Leader}}\n{{2019 Conservative Party leadership election}}\n{{London Conservative Party MPs}}\n}}\n{{Subject bar|portal1=Biography|portal2=Politics|portal20=United Kingdom|portal3=Conservatism|commons=y|commons-search=Category:Boris Johnson|n=y|n-search=Category:Boris Johnson|q=y|q-search=Boris Johnson|d=y|d-search=Q180589|s=y|s-search=Author:Alexander Boris de Pfeffel Johnson}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johnson, Boris}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Boris Johnson| ]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:21st-century Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the Conservative Party (UK)]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs]]\n[[Category:Mayors of London]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) mayors]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2001\u20132005]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2005\u20132010]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2015\u20132017]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2017\u20132019]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Paralympic Order]]\n[[Category:Critics of the European Union]]\n[[Category:People associated with transport in London]]\n[[Category:Political sex scandals in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English magazine editors]]\n[[Category:The Spectator editors]]\n[[Category:Daily Telegraph journalists]]\n[[Category:The Times people]]\n[[Category:20th-century British journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century British journalists]]\n[[Category:English political writers]]\n[[Category:English male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Writers from London]]\n[[Category:20th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English writers]]\n[[Category:American magazine editors]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:People who lost United States citizenship]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Oxford Union]]\n[[Category:People educated at Ashdown House]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:English Anglicans]]\n[[Category:American Anglicans]]\n[[Category:20th-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:Converts to Anglicanism from Roman Catholicism]]\n[[Category:Christians from Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Christians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:English people of American descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:People from Crouch End]]\n[[Category:People from Maida Vale]]\n[[Category:People from Uccle]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Writers from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Politicians from New York City]]\n[[Category:Writers from New York City]]\n[[Category:People from the Upper East Side]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2019\u2013]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the European Schools]]\n", "name_user": "Davide King", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBrexit campaign: 2015\u20132016:hadn't ---> had not", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Johnson"}
{"title_page": "Dilbar (song)", "text_new": "{{short description|Alka Yagnik song}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Dilbar Dilbar\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| artist   = [[Alka Yagnik]]\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n| released = {{Start date|1999|06|11|df=y}}\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| genre    = [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n| length   = {{Duration|m=5|s=46}}\n| label    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer = [[Nadeem\u2013Shravan|Nadeem-Shravan]]\n| lyricist = [[Sameer (lyricist)|Sameer]]\n| producer =\n| misc     = {{External music video|type=song|{{YouTube|eIPrsWWdhSU|\"Dilbar Dilbar\" Sirf Tum}} }}\n}}\n\"'''Dilbar'''\" is a [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood song]], originally released as part of the soundtrack for the [[List of Bollywood films of 1999|1999 Indian film]] ''[[Sirf Tum]]''. The song was originally composed by [[Nadeem\u2013Shravan|Nadeem-Shravan]] and sung by [[Alka Yagnik]], with lyrics by [[Sameer (lyricist)|Sameer]]. The song's original music video features [[Sushmita Sen]] and [[Sanjay Kapoor]].<ref name=\"indianexpress\">{{cite news |title=Shaken, Not Stirred |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/shaken-not-stirred-bollywood-playback-singers-old-classic-music-remakes-5294719/ |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |date=7 August 2018 |language=en-IN}}</ref> The ''Sirf Tum'' [[soundtrack album]] sold 2.2{{nbsp}}million units, and was the ninth best-selling [[Bollywood music]] album of 1999.<ref name=\"boi90s\">{{cite web|title=Music Hits 1990-1999 (Figures in Units)|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=284&catName=MTk5MC0xOTk5|website=[[Box Office India]]|date=2 January 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100102010439/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=284&catName=MTk5MC0xOTk5|archivedate=2 January 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe song was recreated for the 2018 film ''[[Satyameva Jayate (2018 film)|Satyameva Jayate]]'', recomposed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]] with [[Middle Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]] influences, and hung by [[Neha Kakkar]] and [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]. Its music video is as usual an [[item number]], featuring [[Moroccan Canadians|Moroccan-Canadian]] dancer [[Nora Fatehi]] performing Arabic [[belly dancing]]. The song later had an [[Arabic language]] version, sung by Nora Fatehi with [[Moroccan hip hop]] group Fnaire, released on 30 November 2018.\n\n==''Satyameva Jayate'' version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Dilbar \n| cover    = Dilbar cover art.jpeg\n| type     = Song\n| artist   = [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Dhvani Bhanushali]] and [[Ikka Singh]]\n| album    =[[Satyameva Jayate (2018 film)]]\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n| released = {{Start date|2018|07|03|df=y}}\n| format   =\n| genre    = \n*[[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n*[[Middle Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]]\n*[[Indian hip hop|Indian{{nbsp}}hip{{nbsp}}hop]]\n| length   = {{Duration|m=2|s=14}}\n| label    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyricist = \n*[[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n*[[Ikka Singh]]\n| misc     = {{External music video|{{YouTube|n2u81Ujc93g|\"Dilbar - Satyameva Jayate\"}}\n | type = song\n}}\n}}\n\nThe destroyed version of the song was released with the title \"Dilbar\" in Satyameva Jayate under the banner of [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] on 3 July 2018. It was written by [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]] and [[Ikka Singh]], composed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]], and sung by [[Neha Kakkar]] and [[Dhvani Bhanushali]], with rapping by [[Ikka Singh]]. Bagchi made use of the [[Oud]], a fretless [[Middle-Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]] stringed instrument, along with [[Arabic music|Arabic]] drums to re-envision the classic song for the new film.<ref name=\"indianexpress\"/>\n\nThe music video of this song features [[Moroccan Canadians|Moroccan-Canadian]] dancer [[Nora Fatehi]] in an [[item number]]. The video heavily references [[Arabic culture]], and the actor [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]] also makes an appearance.<ref name=\"indianexpress\"/> In the music video, [[Nora Fatehi]] performs [[belly dancing]], an [[Arabic dance]] style that was previously featured in a number of popular Bollywood item numbers, performed by actresses such as [[Helen (actress)|Helen]] in \"Mehbooba O Mehbooba\" from ''[[Sholay]]'' (1975), [[Zeenat Aman]] in \"Raqqasa Mera Naam\" from ''[[The Great Gambler]]'' (1979), [[Mallika Sherawat]] in \"Mayya Mayya\" from ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007), and [[Rani Mukerji]] in \"Aga Bai\" from ''[[Aiyyaa]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rajguru |first1=Sumit |title=International Dance Day 2019: Top 5 belly dance numbers in Bollywood you can't miss |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/280419/international-dance-day-2019-top-5-belly-dance-numbers-in-bollywood-y.html |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\nThe remake received 20 million views on the first day of its [[YouTube]] release.<ref name=\"yodofeed.com\">{{cite web|url=https://yodofeed.com/dilbar-dilbar-remake-is-the-new-make/|title=Dilbar Dilbar : Remake is the new make. - YODO Feed|date=13 July 2018|publisher=}}</ref> It became the first Indian song to reach number three on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' YouTube Music Chart.<ref name=\"hindustantimes_GxYPXbKZxa7g3cx7lm9wRK\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/music/dhvani-bhanushali-s-dilbar-tops-billboard-youtube-chart/story-GxYPXbKZxa7g3cx7lm9wRK.html|title=Dhvani Bhanushali\u2019s Dilbar tops Billboard YouTube chart|date=July 13, 2018|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref><ref name=\"radioandmusic_180711\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/180711-t-series-song-dilbar-trends-3-on-billboard|title=T-Series song 'Dilbar' trends at #3 on Billboard|website=www.radioandmusic.com}}</ref> The ''Satyameva Jayate'' version of the song has received about 1.1{{nbsp}}billion views on [[YouTube]], making it the most-viewed song on the [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benjamin |first1=Jeff |title=Bollywood Channel T-Series Is YouTube's First To Hit 100 Million Subscribers |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2019/05/30/bollywood-youtube-channel-t-series-first-to-hit-100-million-subscribers/ |accessdate=11 June 2019 |work=[[Forbes]] |date=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevansh Sharma from [[Firstpost]] remarked, \"The soul of the new track is Neha Kakkar who brings a sensual-yet-never-raunchy appeal through her vocals. Her range allows her to switch from the meditative stanzas to the uninhibited chorus like a chameleon.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bollywood/satyamev-jayate-music-review-neha-kakkars-dilbar-is-a-clear-winner-but-tanishk-bagchi-can-do-better-4944461.html|title=Satyamev Jayate music review: Neha Kakkar's Dilbar is a clear winner, but Tanishk Bagchi can do better- Entertainment News, Firstpost|publisher=}}</ref> Shravan Shah from Missmalini said, \"The original one was done so well and is so engraved in our hearts that the reprise version just doesn\u2019t match up to it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.missmalini.com/2018/07/04/dilbar-song-nora-fatehi-is-the-only-reason-we-have-this-on-repeat/|title=Dilbar Song: Nora Fatehi Is The Only Reason We Have This On Repeat|date=4 July 2018|publisher=}}</ref> Nora's belly dancing has received wide praise, but the song has also received some mixed reactions from fans of the original song.<ref name=\"t2online_65964\">{{cite web|url=http://t2online.com/t2-digs/nora-fatehi-s-sensuous-belly-dance-in-the-remix-of-90-s-hit-song-dilbar-turns-up-the-heat/cid/659642|title=Fans have mixed reactions to Nora Fatehi's belly dance in the new Dilbar remix|website=t2online.com}}</ref>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Arabic Dilbar==\n\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Arabic Dilbar\n| cover      = Dilbar Arabic Cover.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Nora Fatehi]] and Fnaire\n| album      =\n| language   = {{Flatlist|\n*[[Arabic]]\n*[[English language|English]]\n*[[Hindi]]\n*[[French language|French]]\n}}\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|11|30|df=y}}\n| format     =\n| genre      = \n*[[Arabic pop]]\n*[[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n*[[Moroccan hip hop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=51}}\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer   = Mohcine Tizaf\n| lyricist   = \n*Khalifa Mennani\n*Achraf Aarab\n| producer   = [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|108FB3SLuk|\"Dilbar Arabic Version\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"Arabic Dilbar\" is the [[Arabic language]] version of this song, featuring a mix of three languages (Arabic, Hindi, and French),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/did-you-know/did-you-know-that-the-arabic-version-of-nora-fatehis-dilbar-is-a-mix-of-three-languages/articleshow/66814931.cms|title=Did you know that the Arabic version of Nora Fatehi's 'Dilbar' is a mix of three languages? - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> was released on November 30, 2018 under the banner of [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]. Nora Fatehi made her debut as a singer in this song,<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/nora-fatehi-on-dilbars-arabic-version-it-was-great-to-mix-two-cultures-it-is-a-cosmopolitan-project/articleshow/66851370.cms|title=Nora Fatehi on Dilbar's Arabic version: It was great to mix two cultures, it is a cosmopolitan project|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-nora-fatehi-to-make-her-singing-debut-with-arabic-version-of-dilbar-2666237&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjAQegQIAxAB&usg=AOvVaw32sIdHI4pkdxn7siuGVCZL|title=Nora Fatehi to make her singing debut with Arabic version of 'Dilbar'|date=22 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/post-dilbar-success-nora-fatehi-set-to-make-her-singing-debut-with-a-revised-version-of-the-song/286939&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjAPegQIAhAB&usg=AOvVaw3aQss_PdA0YakKI1zVnFYE|title=Latest Bollywood News & Gossip - Hollywood News and Celebrity News - Times Now News|first=|last=TimesNow|website=TimesNow}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/nora-fatehi-to-debut-as-singer/articleshow/65868458.cms&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjANegQICxAB&usg=AOvVaw3nBuOQrvhBE9kJZ5xA-ykJ|title=Page Not Found|website=m.timesofindia.com}}</ref> as a collaboration with [[Moroccan hip hop]] group Fnaire. The song was composed by Mohcine Tizaf, with lyrics by Khalifa Mennani and Achraf Aarab, and the performance in the video for the release was choreographed by Caeser Gonsalves.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/dilbar-arabic-version-nora-fatehi-again-steals-the-hearts-with-her-dance-moves/articleshow/66882686.cms|title=Dilbar Arabic Version: Nora Fatehi again steals the hearts with her dance moves - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nWhereas the ''Satyameva Jayate'' music video heavily referenced Arabic culture, the music video for the Arabic version instead heavily references [[Indian culture]]. In contrast to the Arabic belly dancing in the ''Satyameva Jayate'' video, Nora Fatehi and Fnaire instead perform standard [[Bollywood dance]] routines in the Arabic version.\n\n===Reception===\nAccording to ''[[Zee News]]'', \"The song easily crossed 100 million views on YouTube within days of its release and no sooner was the social media flooded with several mashups and dance videos.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/music/nora-fatehis-arabic-version-of-dilbar-song-is-out-and-its-got-us-hooked-watch-2159941.html|title=Nora Fatehi's Arabic version of 'Dilbar' song is out and it's got us hooked\u2014Watch|date=30 November 2018|publisher=}}</ref> Srishti Kapoor of Mumbai Mirror said, \"Her debut song as a pop artist in the Middle East and North Africa, just like the original, will make one want to dance. What makes it unique though, is the use of Moroccan instruments.\"<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{T-Series}}\n[[Category:1999 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:Alka Yagnik songs]]\n[[Category:Arabic-language songs]]\n[[Category:French-language songs]]\n[[Category:Hindi film songs]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language songs]]\n[[Category:Moroccan songs]]\n[[Category:Multilingual songs]]\n[[Category:Neha Kakkar songs]]\n[[Category:Dhvani Bhanushali songs]] \n[[Category:Pop-folk songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written for films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Alka Yagnik song}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Dilbar Dilbar\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| artist   = [[Alka Yagnik]]\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n| released = {{Start date|1999|06|11|df=y}}\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| genre    = [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n| length   = {{Duration|m=5|s=46}}\n| label    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer = [[Nadeem\u2013Shravan|Nadeem-Shravan]]\n| lyricist = [[Sameer (lyricist)|Sameer]]\n| producer =\n| misc     = {{External music video|type=song|{{YouTube|eIPrsWWdhSU|\"Dilbar Dilbar\" Sirf Tum}} }}\n}}\n\"'''Dilbar'''\" is a [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood song]], originally released as part of the soundtrack for the [[List of Bollywood films of 1999|1999 Indian film]] ''[[Sirf Tum]]''. The song was originally composed by [[Nadeem\u2013Shravan|Nadeem-Shravan]] and sung by [[Alka Yagnik]], with lyrics by [[Sameer (lyricist)|Sameer]]. The song's original music video features [[Sushmita Sen]] and [[Sanjay Kapoor]].<ref name=\"indianexpress\">{{cite news |title=Shaken, Not Stirred |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/shaken-not-stirred-bollywood-playback-singers-old-classic-music-remakes-5294719/ |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |date=7 August 2018 |language=en-IN}}</ref> The ''Sirf Tum'' [[soundtrack album]] sold 2.2{{nbsp}}million units, and was the ninth best-selling [[Bollywood music]] album of 1999.<ref name=\"boi90s\">{{cite web|title=Music Hits 1990-1999 (Figures in Units)|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=284&catName=MTk5MC0xOTk5|website=[[Box Office India]]|date=2 January 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100102010439/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=284&catName=MTk5MC0xOTk5|archivedate=2 January 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe song was destroyed for the 2018 film ''[[Satyameva Jayate (2018 film)|Satyameva Jayate]]'', basterdised by [[Tanishk Bagchi]] with [[Middle Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]] influences, and hung by [[Neha Kakkar]] and [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]. Its music video is as usual an [[item number]], featuring [[Moroccan Canadians|Moroccan-Canadian]] dancer [[Nora Fatehi]] performing Arabic [[belly dancing]]. The song later had an [[Arabic language]] version, sung by Nora Fatehi with [[Moroccan hip hop]] group Fnaire, released on 30 November 2018.\n\n==''Satyameva Jayate'' version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Dilbar \n| cover    = Dilbar cover art.jpeg\n| type     = Song\n| artist   = [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Dhvani Bhanushali]] and [[Ikka Singh]]\n| album    =[[Satyameva Jayate (2018 film)]]\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n| released = {{Start date|2018|07|03|df=y}}\n| format   =\n| genre    = \n*[[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n*[[Middle Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]]\n*[[Indian hip hop|Indian{{nbsp}}hip{{nbsp}}hop]]\n| length   = {{Duration|m=2|s=14}}\n| label    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyricist = \n*[[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n*[[Ikka Singh]]\n| misc     = {{External music video|{{YouTube|n2u81Ujc93g|\"Dilbar - Satyameva Jayate\"}}\n | type = song\n}}\n}}\n\nThe destroyed version of the song was released with the title \"Dilbar\" in Satyameva Jayate under the banner of [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] on 3 July 2018. It was written by [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]] and [[Ikka Singh]], composed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]], and sung by [[Neha Kakkar]] and [[Dhvani Bhanushali]], with rapping by [[Ikka Singh]]. Bagchi made use of the [[Oud]], a fretless [[Middle-Eastern music|Middle-Eastern]] stringed instrument, along with [[Arabic music|Arabic]] drums to re-envision the classic song for the new film.<ref name=\"indianexpress\"/>\n\nThe music video of this song features [[Moroccan Canadians|Moroccan-Canadian]] dancer [[Nora Fatehi]] in an [[item number]]. The video heavily references [[Arabic culture]], and the actor [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]] also makes an appearance.<ref name=\"indianexpress\"/> In the music video, [[Nora Fatehi]] performs [[belly dancing]], an [[Arabic dance]] style that was previously featured in a number of popular Bollywood item numbers, performed by actresses such as [[Helen (actress)|Helen]] in \"Mehbooba O Mehbooba\" from ''[[Sholay]]'' (1975), [[Zeenat Aman]] in \"Raqqasa Mera Naam\" from ''[[The Great Gambler]]'' (1979), [[Mallika Sherawat]] in \"Mayya Mayya\" from ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007), and [[Rani Mukerji]] in \"Aga Bai\" from ''[[Aiyyaa]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rajguru |first1=Sumit |title=International Dance Day 2019: Top 5 belly dance numbers in Bollywood you can't miss |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/280419/international-dance-day-2019-top-5-belly-dance-numbers-in-bollywood-y.html |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\nThe remake received 20 million views on the first day of its [[YouTube]] release.<ref name=\"yodofeed.com\">{{cite web|url=https://yodofeed.com/dilbar-dilbar-remake-is-the-new-make/|title=Dilbar Dilbar : Remake is the new make. - YODO Feed|date=13 July 2018|publisher=}}</ref> It became the first Indian song to reach number three on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' YouTube Music Chart.<ref name=\"hindustantimes_GxYPXbKZxa7g3cx7lm9wRK\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/music/dhvani-bhanushali-s-dilbar-tops-billboard-youtube-chart/story-GxYPXbKZxa7g3cx7lm9wRK.html|title=Dhvani Bhanushali\u2019s Dilbar tops Billboard YouTube chart|date=July 13, 2018|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref><ref name=\"radioandmusic_180711\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/180711-t-series-song-dilbar-trends-3-on-billboard|title=T-Series song 'Dilbar' trends at #3 on Billboard|website=www.radioandmusic.com}}</ref> The ''Satyameva Jayate'' version of the song has received about 1.1{{nbsp}}billion views on [[YouTube]], making it the most-viewed song on the [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benjamin |first1=Jeff |title=Bollywood Channel T-Series Is YouTube's First To Hit 100 Million Subscribers |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2019/05/30/bollywood-youtube-channel-t-series-first-to-hit-100-million-subscribers/ |accessdate=11 June 2019 |work=[[Forbes]] |date=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevansh Sharma from [[Firstpost]] remarked, \"The soul of the new track is Neha Kakkar who brings a sensual-yet-never-raunchy appeal through her vocals. Her range allows her to switch from the meditative stanzas to the uninhibited chorus like a chameleon.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bollywood/satyamev-jayate-music-review-neha-kakkars-dilbar-is-a-clear-winner-but-tanishk-bagchi-can-do-better-4944461.html|title=Satyamev Jayate music review: Neha Kakkar's Dilbar is a clear winner, but Tanishk Bagchi can do better- Entertainment News, Firstpost|publisher=}}</ref> Shravan Shah from Missmalini said, \"The original one was done so well and is so engraved in our hearts that the reprise version just doesn\u2019t match up to it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.missmalini.com/2018/07/04/dilbar-song-nora-fatehi-is-the-only-reason-we-have-this-on-repeat/|title=Dilbar Song: Nora Fatehi Is The Only Reason We Have This On Repeat|date=4 July 2018|publisher=}}</ref> Nora's belly dancing has received wide praise, but the song has also received some mixed reactions from fans of the original song.<ref name=\"t2online_65964\">{{cite web|url=http://t2online.com/t2-digs/nora-fatehi-s-sensuous-belly-dance-in-the-remix-of-90-s-hit-song-dilbar-turns-up-the-heat/cid/659642|title=Fans have mixed reactions to Nora Fatehi's belly dance in the new Dilbar remix|website=t2online.com}}</ref>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Arabic Dilbar==\n\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Arabic Dilbar\n| cover      = Dilbar Arabic Cover.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Nora Fatehi]] and Fnaire\n| album      =\n| language   = {{Flatlist|\n*[[Arabic]]\n*[[English language|English]]\n*[[Hindi]]\n*[[French language|French]]\n}}\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|11|30|df=y}}\n| format     =\n| genre      = \n*[[Arabic pop]]\n*[[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]]\n*[[Moroccan hip hop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=51}}\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| composer   = Mohcine Tizaf\n| lyricist   = \n*Khalifa Mennani\n*Achraf Aarab\n| producer   = [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|108FB3SLuk|\"Dilbar Arabic Version\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"Arabic Dilbar\" is the [[Arabic language]] version of this song, featuring a mix of three languages (Arabic, Hindi, and French),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/did-you-know/did-you-know-that-the-arabic-version-of-nora-fatehis-dilbar-is-a-mix-of-three-languages/articleshow/66814931.cms|title=Did you know that the Arabic version of Nora Fatehi's 'Dilbar' is a mix of three languages? - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> was released on November 30, 2018 under the banner of [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]. Nora Fatehi made her debut as a singer in this song,<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/nora-fatehi-on-dilbars-arabic-version-it-was-great-to-mix-two-cultures-it-is-a-cosmopolitan-project/articleshow/66851370.cms|title=Nora Fatehi on Dilbar's Arabic version: It was great to mix two cultures, it is a cosmopolitan project|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-nora-fatehi-to-make-her-singing-debut-with-arabic-version-of-dilbar-2666237&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjAQegQIAxAB&usg=AOvVaw32sIdHI4pkdxn7siuGVCZL|title=Nora Fatehi to make her singing debut with Arabic version of 'Dilbar'|date=22 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/post-dilbar-success-nora-fatehi-set-to-make-her-singing-debut-with-a-revised-version-of-the-song/286939&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjAPegQIAhAB&usg=AOvVaw3aQss_PdA0YakKI1zVnFYE|title=Latest Bollywood News & Gossip - Hollywood News and Celebrity News - Times Now News|first=|last=TimesNow|website=TimesNow}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/nora-fatehi-to-debut-as-singer/articleshow/65868458.cms&sa=U&ved=2ahUKEwjQkayWoYbfAhUDE7wKHUa7DXQQFjANegQICxAB&usg=AOvVaw3nBuOQrvhBE9kJZ5xA-ykJ|title=Page Not Found|website=m.timesofindia.com}}</ref> as a collaboration with [[Moroccan hip hop]] group Fnaire. The song was composed by Mohcine Tizaf, with lyrics by Khalifa Mennani and Achraf Aarab, and the performance in the video for the release was choreographed by Caeser Gonsalves.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/dilbar-arabic-version-nora-fatehi-again-steals-the-hearts-with-her-dance-moves/articleshow/66882686.cms|title=Dilbar Arabic Version: Nora Fatehi again steals the hearts with her dance moves - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nWhereas the ''Satyameva Jayate'' music video heavily referenced Arabic culture, the music video for the Arabic version instead heavily references [[Indian culture]]. In contrast to the Arabic belly dancing in the ''Satyameva Jayate'' video, Nora Fatehi and Fnaire instead perform standard [[Bollywood dance]] routines in the Arabic version.\n\n===Reception===\nAccording to ''[[Zee News]]'', \"The song easily crossed 100 million views on YouTube within days of its release and no sooner was the social media flooded with several mashups and dance videos.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/music/nora-fatehis-arabic-version-of-dilbar-song-is-out-and-its-got-us-hooked-watch-2159941.html|title=Nora Fatehi's Arabic version of 'Dilbar' song is out and it's got us hooked\u2014Watch|date=30 November 2018|publisher=}}</ref> Srishti Kapoor of Mumbai Mirror said, \"Her debut song as a pop artist in the Middle East and North Africa, just like the original, will make one want to dance. What makes it unique though, is the use of Moroccan instruments.\"<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{T-Series}}\n[[Category:1999 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:Alka Yagnik songs]]\n[[Category:Arabic-language songs]]\n[[Category:French-language songs]]\n[[Category:Hindi film songs]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language songs]]\n[[Category:Moroccan songs]]\n[[Category:Multilingual songs]]\n[[Category:Neha Kakkar songs]]\n[[Category:Dhvani Bhanushali songs]] \n[[Category:Pop-folk songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written for films]]\n", "name_user": "Shish Kar", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dilbar_(song)"}
{"title_page": "Montenegro national football team records and statistics", "text_new": "As a member of FIFA and UEFA, [[Montenegro national football team]] is playing official matches since March 2007. Montenegro is playing in the qualifiers for FIFA World Cup and UEFA European Championship. Except that, the team is playing friendly matches.\n\n==Matches and records==\n{{Main|List of official matches of the Montenegro national football team}}\n\n=== Records ===\n;Largest home victory: '''5-0''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|KAZ}}, 8 October 2016, [[Podgorica]]\n;Largest away victory: '''0-6''', {{fb|SMR}} \u2013 {{fb|MNE}}, 11 September 2012, [[Serravalle (San Marino)|Serravalle]]\n;Largest home defeat: '''0-4''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|UKR}}, 28 March 2013, [[Podgorica]]; '''1-5''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|ENG}}, 25 March 2019, [[Podgorica]]\n;Largest away defeat: '''7-0''', {{fb|ENG}} \u2013 {{fb|MNE}}, 14 November 2019, [[Wembley Stadium|London]]\n;Longest winning streak: '''4 matches''', (11 August 2010 - 12 October 2010; 11 September 2012 - 26 March 2013)\n;Longest streak without defeat: '''8 matches''', (11 August 2010 - 10 August 2011)\n;Longest losing streak: '''4 matches''', (9 October 2015 - 29 March 2016)\n;Longest streak without win: '''7 matches''', (9 October 2015 - 8 October 2016; 5 October 2017 - 10 September 2018)\n;Highest home attendance: '''13,000''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|ENG}} 1-1, 26 March 2013, [[Podgorica]]\n;Highest away attendance: '''83,807''', {{fb|ENG}} \u2013 {{bk|MNE}} 4-1, 11 October 2013, [[London]]\n\n===Competition record===\nBelow is a list of games of Montenegro national football team by every competition on which they participated.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Competition\n! G\n! W\n! D\n! L\n! GF\n! GA\n! GD\n|-\n|[[FIFA World Cup]] qualifiers\n|'''30'''\n| 10\n| 10\n| 10\n| 47\n| 43\n| +4\n|-\n|[[UEFA European Championship]] qualifiers\n|'''28'''\n| 6\n| 8\n| 14\n| 20\n| 45\n| -25\n|-\n|[[UEF