[[Category:2007\u201308 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2008\u201309 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2010\u201311 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2011\u201312 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2012\u201313 in Montenegrin football]]\n[[Category:2013\u201314 in Montenegrin football]]\n", "text_old": "As a member of FIFA and UEFA, [[Montenegro national football team]] is playing official matches since March 2007. Montenegro is playing in the qualifiers for FIFA World Cup and UEFA European Championship. Except that, the team is playing friendly matches.\n\n==Matches and records==\n{{Main|List of official matches of the Montenegro national football team}}\n\n=== Records ===\n;Largest home victory: '''5-0''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|KAZ}}, 8 October 2016, [[Podgorica]]\n;Largest away victory: '''0-6''', {{fb|SMR}} \u2013 {{fb|MNE}}, 11 September 2012, [[Serravalle (San Marino)|Serravalle]]\n;Largest home defeat: '''0-4''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|UKR}}, 28 March 2013, [[Podgorica]]; '''1-5''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|ENG}}, 25 March 2019, [[Podgorica]]\n;Largest away defeat: '''7-0''', {{fb|ENG}} \u2013 {{fb|MNE}}, 14 November 2019, [[Wembley Stadium|London]]\n;Longest winning streak: '''4 matches''', (11 August 2010 - 12 October 2010; 11 September 2012 - 26 March 2013)\n;Longest streak without defeat: '''8 matches''', (11 August 2010 - 10 August 2011)\n;Longest losing streak: '''4 matches''', (9 October 2015 - 29 March 2016)\n;Longest streak without win: '''7 matches''', (9 October 2015 - 8 October 2016; 5 October 2017 - 10 September 2018)\n;Highest home attendance: '''13,000''', {{fb|MNE}} \u2013 {{fb|ENG}} 1-1, 26 March 2013, [[Podgorica]]\n;Highest away attendance: '''83,807''', {{fb|ENG}} \u2013 {{bk|MNE}} 4-1, 11 October 2013, [[London]]\n\n===Competition record===\nBelow is a list of games of Montenegro national football team by every competition on which they participated.\n{| class=\"wikitable 