{"title_page": "Meldan", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Meldan\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u041c\u0435\u043b\u0434\u0430\u043d\u044c\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vologodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|22|N|39|08|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vologodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Meldan''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u043b\u0434\u0430\u043d\u044c}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Kubenskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vologodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vologda]] is 67 km, to Kubenskoye is 30 km. Pavshino is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vologodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologodsky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Meldan\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u041c\u0435\u043b\u0434\u0430\u043d\u044c\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vologodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|22|N|39|08|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vologodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Meldan''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u043b\u0434\u0430\u043d\u044c}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Kubenskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vologodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vologda]] is 67 km, to Kubenskoye is 30 km. Pavshino is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vologodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologodsky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meldan"}
{"title_page": "The Split (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|British television legal drama series}}\n{{about|the British TV series|the Israeli TV series|Split (TV series)}}\n{{use British English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = The Split\n| image = [[File:TheSplittitlecard.jpg|250px]]\n| caption =\n| genre =\n| creator = [[Abi Morgan]]<ref name=\"variety1\" />\n| director = Jessica Hobbs<ref name=\"variety1\" />\n| starring = {{plainlist|\n* [[Nicola Walker]]\n* [[Stephen Mangan]]\n* [[Fiona Button]]\n* [[Annabel Scholey]]\n* [[Barry Atsma]]\n* [[Deborah Findlay]]\n}}\n| writer = {{plainlist|\n* Abi Morgan<ref name=variety1/>\n* Jane Eden\n* Louise Ironside\n}}\n| composer = Isobel Waller-Bridge\n| language = English\n| country = United Kingdom\n| location = \n| executive_producer = {{plainlist|\n* [[Jane Featherstone]]<ref name=variety1/>\n* Abi Morgan\n* Jessica Hobbs\n* Lucy Richer\n}}\n| producer = Lucy Dyke<ref name=variety1/>\n| runtime = 60 minutes (inc. adverts)\n| company = Sister Pictures\n| picture_format = [[Univisium|2:1]] [[1080p]]\n| network  = {{plainlist|\n* [[BBC One]] (UK)\n* [[SundanceTV]] (US)\n}}\n| distributor = [[BBC Worldwide]]\n| audio_format = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2018|4|24|df=yes}}\n| last_aired = present\n| num_series = 2\n| num_episodes = 12\n| list_episodes = #Episodes\n}}\n\n'''''The Split''''' is a British television [[legal drama]] series, written and created by [[Abi Morgan]], that first broadcast in the [[United Kingdom]] on [[BBC One]] on 24 April 2018. The six-part series, commissioned in August 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/08/thandie-newton-line-of-duty-abi-morgan-split-bbc-one-drama-orders-1201808013/|title=BBC One Orders Drama 'The Split' From Abi Morgan; Thandie Newton Joins 'Line Of Duty' Season 4 \u2013 Edinburgh|work=Deadline.com|date=24 August 2016|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione}}</ref> follows the lives of the Defoe family, who all work in divorce law for the family firm, aside from eldest sister Hannah ([[Nicola Walker]]), who works for rival family law firm Noble & Hale and youngest daughter who is a child minder.<ref name=deadline1>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/the-split-sundancetv-bbc-one-cast-for-abi-morgan-drama-series-1202121017/|title='The Split': SundanceTV & BBC One Round Out Cast For Abi Morgan Drama Series|work=Deadline.com|date=28 June 2017|first=Denise|last=Petski}}</ref> The series co-stars [[Stephen Mangan]], [[Fiona Button]], [[Annabel Scholey]] and [[Barry Atsma]].<ref name=deadline1/>\n\nProduction for the first series began in July 2017 in [[London]].<ref name=deadline1/> On 13 January 2017, [[SundanceTV]] announced that it would be partnering with the [[BBC]] to produce the series.<ref name=variety1/> [[SundanceTV]] will thus hold exclusive rights for broadcast in the [[United States]].<ref name=variety1>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/sundance-tv-abi-morgan-the-split-bbc-1201960036/|title=SundanceTV Partners With BBC One for Abi Morgan's 'The Split'|date=13 January 2017|work=Variety|first=Oriana|last=Schwindt}}</ref> Series 1 was released on DVD on 4 June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.amazon.co.uk/The-Split-DVD/dp/B07C5P8Q2S |title= The Split|date= 4 June 2018 |via= Amazon }}</ref>\n\nA  second series was commissioned in May 2018 <ref>[https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/967120/The-Split-series-2-BBC-air-date-cast-trailer-plot-Nicola-Walker-renewed-confirmed The Split series 2 BBC air date, cast, trailer, plot] by Emma Nolan,  May 30, 2018</ref> with production beginning in March 2019<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/the-split-s2|title=BBC - Second series of Abi Morgan\u2019s original BBC One drama The Split begins production - Media Centre|website=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> Series 2 sees the return of the Defoe family at newly merged law firm Noble Hale Defoe, with most of the original cast confirmed.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/>  [[Donna Air]] and [[Ben Bailey Smith]]  have been announced as joining the cast for the second series as high profile clients for the law firm<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-03-21/the-split-series-2-donna-air-joins-cast-filming-begins/|title=Donna Air lands role in The Split as second series goes into production|website=Radio Times}}</ref> and [[Damien Molony]] as the character Tyler Donaghue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://damienmolony.org/2019/07/11/new-tv-role-exclusive-damien-molony-joins-bbc-one-legal-drama-the-split-series-2/|title=NEW TV ROLE EXCLUSIVE: Damien Molony joins BBC One legal drama \u2018The Split\u2019|date=11 July 2019}}</ref> The first episode of series 2 aired on BBC One on 11 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvwise.co.uk/2020/01/bbc-one-sets-premiere-date-for-the-split-for-season-2/|title=BBC One Sets Premiere Date For 'The Split' For Season 2|date=29 January 2020}}</ref> During filming Series 2, production visited [[The Maidstone Studios|Maidstone TV Studios]] to film a studio show segment. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/filmed-in-kent/2020/02/the-split-series-2-2020/|title=Kent Film Office The Split article|author=Kent Film Office|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{See also|List of The Split characters}}\n===Main cast===\n* [[Nicola Walker]] as [[List of The Split characters#Hannah Stern|Hannah Stern]], a divorce lawyer working for Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Stephen Mangan]] as [[List of The Split characters#Nathan Stern|Nathan Stern]], Hannah's husband, a [[barrister]]<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Fiona Button]] as [[List of The Split characters#Rose Defoe|Rose Defoe]], Hannah's youngest sister.<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Annabel Scholey]] as [[List of The Split characters#Nina Defoe|Nina Defoe]], Hannah's younger sister, a fellow divorce lawyer for Defoe's, the family practice<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Barry Atsma]] as [[List of The Split characters#Christie Carmichael|Christie Carmichael]], Hannah's former boyfriend who also works for Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Stephen Tompkinson]] as [[List of The Split characters#Davey McKenzie|Davey McKenzie]], a millionaire divorcing his wife (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Meera Syal]] as [[List of The Split characters#Goldie McKenzie|Goldie McKenzie]], Davey's wife and his company's secretary (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Anthony Head]] as [[List of The Split characters#Oscar Defoe|Oscar Defoe]], Hannah's long lost father (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Deborah Findlay]] as [[List of The Split characters#Ruth Defoe|Ruth Defoe]], Hannah's mother, the director of the family firm<ref name=deadline1/> \n* [[Rudi Dharmalingam]] as [[List of The Split characters#James Cutler|James Cutler]], Rose\u2019s [[fianc\u00e9]], later husband<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Donna Air]] as [[List of The Split characters#Fi Hansen|Fi Hansen]], a famous presenter divorcing her husband (Series 2)<ref name=inews>{{cite web |url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/television/the-split-season-2-cast-nicola-walker-new-series-episodes-bbc-one-when-start-time-1387255 |title=The Split season 2 cast: who stars with Nicola Walker in the new series, and when it starts on BBC One tonight |last=Selby |first=Jenn |date=11 February 2020 |website=i News |publisher= |access-date=22 February 2020 |quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Bailey Smith]] as [[List of The Split characters#Richie Hansen|Richie Hansen]], Fi's husband (Series 2)<ref name=\"inews\"/>\n\n===Supporting cast===\n* [[Chukwudi Iwuji]] as [[List of The Split characters#Zander Hale|Alexander 'Zander' Hale]], director of Noble & Hale <ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Kobna Holdbrook-Smith]] as [[List of The Split characters#Glen Peters|Glen Peters]], the [[vicar (Anglicanism)|vicar]] performing Rose and James' wedding ceremony (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Maggie O'Neill]] as [[List of The Split characters#Yvonne Duchy|Yvonne Duchy]], Goldie's best friend, who is having an affair with her husband (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Josette Simon]] as [[List of The Split characters#Maya|Maya]], Oscar Defoe's second partner (Series 1)\n* [[Mathew Baynton]] as [[List of The Split characters#Rex Pope|Rex Pope]], a stand-up comedian <ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Damien Molony]] as [[List of The Split characters#Tyler Donaghue|Tyler Donaghue]], Zander's fianc\u00e9 (Series 2)\n* Elizabeth Roberts as [[List of The Split characters#Liv Stern|Liv Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's elder daughter<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Mollie Cowen as [[List of The Split characters#Tilly Stern|Tilly Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's younger daughter<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Toby Oliver as [[List of The Split characters#Vinnie Stern|Vinnie Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's son<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Ellora Torchia as [[List of The Split characters#Maggie Lavelle|Maggie Lavelle]], a paralegal at Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Brenock O'Connor as [[List of The Split characters#Sasha|Sasha]], Liv Stern's boyfriend (Series 1)\n* [[Ian McElhinney]] as [[List of The Split characters#Sasha|Prof Ronnie]], a friend of Hannah Stern's mother (Series 2) \n* [[Chanel Cresswell]] as Kelsey Ashworth (Series 1, episode 2)\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| color1     = #B0C4DE\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1  = 6\n| start1     = {{Start date|2018|4|24|df=y}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2018|5|29|df=y}}\n\n| color2     = #000000\n| link2      = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2  = 6\n| start2     = {{Start date|2020|2|11|df=y}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2020|3|17|df=y}}\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |background=#B0C4DE |overall=6 |series=6 |title=23 |director=20 |writer=20 |airdate=15 |viewers=10 |country=U.K |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=1\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title= Episode 1\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|4|24|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 6.89<ref name=\"Barb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-30/|title=Weekly Top 30 Programmes|publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|access-date=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= Hannah represents the ex-wife of top stand-up comedian Rex Pope ([[Mathew Baynton]]) who has engaged in a legal battle to try to prevent him from using material referencing her in his new stand-up arena tour, and also takes on one of her mother's former clients, Davey McKenzie ([[Stephen Tompkinson]]), who has issued divorce proceedings against wife Goldie ([[Meera Syal]]) after more than twenty years of marriage. Hannah's long-lost father, Oscar ([[Anthony Head]]) also returns after a thirty year absence to reclaim his stake in the family business.\n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=2\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title= Episode 2\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|5|1|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 5.62<ref name=\"Barb\"/>\n |ShortSummary= Hannah tries to negotiate the pre-nup of Premier League footballer Diallo Diapo (Thierry Mabonga), who has a chequered history of adultery, but proceedings are hindered by the arrival of Diallo's lawyer, who just happens to be Christie's pregnant ex-wife Lauren Brooker ([[Ruth Bradley]]). Meanwhile, Oscar tries to win back the affection of his children by wining and dining them at a swanky London hotel, and the McKenzie divorce grows increasingly bitter when further relevations boil to the surface.\n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=3\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title= Episode 3\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan & Jane Eden\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|5|8|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 5.38<ref name=\"Barb\"/>\n |ShortSummary= Hannah represents Jaynie Lee ([[Tamara Lawrance]]), a high-flying businesswoman whose frozen embryos are under threat from her husband as deliberations over their divorce settlement threaten to turn ugly. Goldie discovers that Davey has an illegitimate child that he fathered ten years ago. Oscar's return continues to drive a wedge into the Defoe family dynamic. Nathan drunkenly tries to accost Nina after revealing that he no longer has sex with Hannah, and after losing her engagement ring, Rose finds herself in a compromising position with vicar Glen (Kobna Holdbrook-Smith).\n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=4\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title= Episode 4\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|5|15|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 5.26<ref name=\"Barb\"/>\n |ShortSummary= The marriage of foreign secretary Emma Graham ([[Claire Rushbrook]]) and her husband Bill ([[Nicholas Gleaves]]) threatens to collapse when a 'wikileaks' style data breach of the names of members of an extra-marital affairs website threatens to reach the tabloids. Ruth holds a dinner party in celebration of Rose's impending nuptials, but the evening descends into disaster when a drunken Nina fails to watch her mouth and berates both Rose and Nathan for their marital indiscretions. \n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=5\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title= Episode 5\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan & Louise Ironside\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|5|22|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 5.69<ref name=\"Barb\"/>\n |ShortSummary= Rose's engagement to James is left in tatters and Hannah struggles to pick up the pieces of her own marriage as the fallout from Nina's revelations continue. Nina discovers that the family business is effectively bankrupt and urges Ruth to sell while the market is still viable. Goldie turns down a settlement offer from Davey, but events take an unexpected turn when the pair end up spending the night together. Nina turns to Rex Pope for comfort, while Hannah is forced to confront her feelings for Christie after discovering that Nathan's indiscretions amount to more than just signing up to a dating website.\n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=6\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title= Episode 6\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|5|29|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 5.54<ref name=\"Barb\"/>\n |ShortSummary= D-Day arrives for the McKenzies as their bitter divorce finally comes to a head, but Hannah is left torn between her head and her heart after learning that losing the case could potentially spark the end of Defoes. James and Rose's wedding day goes off without a hitch, but after learning that Christie is to take up a new job in Chicago, the celebrations force Hannah to finally make a decision about the future of her marriage. \n |LineColor=B0C4DE\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 2 (2020)=== \n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall=6 |season=6 |title=23 |director=20 |writer=20 |airdate=15 |viewers=10 |country=U.K |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Episode 1\n |DirectedBy      = Paula Van Der Oest\n |WrittenBy       = Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|11|df=y}}\n |Viewers         = 5.19\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Episode 2\n |DirectedBy      = Paula Van Der Oest\n |WrittenBy       = Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|18|df=y}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Episode 3\n |DirectedBy      = Paula Van Der Oest\n |WrittenBy       = Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|25|df=y}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Episode 4\n |DirectedBy      = Paula Van Der Oest\n |WrittenBy       = Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|2|df=y}}<ref name=\"BBC One on Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BBCOne/status/1232425035140235264|title=BBC One on Twitter|publisher=BBC One|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 11\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Episode 5\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|10|df=y}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Episode 6\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|17|df=y}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme|id=b0b15b16|title=The Split}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=7631146|title=The Split}}\n\n{{BBC Television}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Split (TV series), The}}\n[[Category:2018 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s British drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s British legal television series]]\n[[Category:2020s British drama television series]]\n[[Category:2020s British legal television series]]\n[[Category:BBC television dramas]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series about marriage]]\n[[Category:Television series about sisters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British television legal drama series}}\n{{about|the British TV series|the Israeli TV series|Split (TV series)}}\n{{use British English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = The Split\n| image = [[File:TheSplittitlecard.jpg|250px]]\n| caption =\n| genre =\n| creator = [[Abi Morgan]]<ref name=\"variety1\" />\n| director = Jessica Hobbs<ref name=\"variety1\" />\n| starring = {{plainlist|\n* [[Nicola Walker]]\n* [[Stephen Mangan]]\n* [[Fiona Button]]\n* [[Annabel Scholey]]\n* [[Barry Atsma]]\n* [[Deborah Findlay]]\n}}\n| writer = {{plainlist|\n* Abi Morgan<ref name=variety1/>\n* Jane Eden\n* Louise Ironside\n}}\n| composer = Isobel Waller-Bridge\n| language = English\n| country = United Kingdom\n| location = \n| executive_producer = {{plainlist|\n* [[Jane Featherstone]]<ref name=variety1/>\n* Abi Morgan\n* Jessica Hobbs\n* Lucy Richer\n}}\n| producer = Lucy Dyke<ref name=variety1/>\n| runtime = 60 minutes (inc. adverts)\n| company = Sister Pictures\n| picture_format = [[Univisium|2:1]] [[1080p]]\n| network  = {{plainlist|\n* [[BBC One]] (UK)\n* [[SundanceTV]] (US)\n}}\n| distributor = [[BBC Worldwide]]\n| audio_format = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2018|4|24|df=yes}}\n| last_aired = present\n| num_series = 2\n| num_episodes = 12\n| list_episodes = #Episodes\n}}\n\n'''''The Split''''' is a British television [[legal drama]] series, written and created by [[Abi Morgan]], that first broadcast in the [[United Kingdom]] on [[BBC One]] on 24 April 2018. The six-part series, commissioned in August 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/08/thandie-newton-line-of-duty-abi-morgan-split-bbc-one-drama-orders-1201808013/|title=BBC One Orders Drama 'The Split' From Abi Morgan; Thandie Newton Joins 'Line Of Duty' Season 4 \u2013 Edinburgh|work=Deadline.com|date=24 August 2016|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione}}</ref> follows the lives of the Defoe family, who all work in divorce law for the family firm, aside from eldest sister Hannah ([[Nicola Walker]]), who works for rival family law firm Noble & Hale and youngest daughter who is a child minder.<ref name=deadline1>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/the-split-sundancetv-bbc-one-cast-for-abi-morgan-drama-series-1202121017/|title='The Split': SundanceTV & BBC One Round Out Cast For Abi Morgan Drama Series|work=Deadline.com|date=28 June 2017|first=Denise|last=Petski}}</ref> The series co-stars [[Stephen Mangan]], [[Fiona Button]], [[Annabel Scholey]] and [[Barry Atsma]].<ref name=deadline1/>\n\nProduction for the first series began in July 2017 in [[London]].<ref name=deadline1/> On 13 January 2017, [[SundanceTV]] announced that it would be partnering with the [[BBC]] to produce the series.<ref name=variety1/> [[SundanceTV]] will thus hold exclusive rights for broadcast in the [[United States]].<ref name=variety1>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/sundance-tv-abi-morgan-the-split-bbc-1201960036/|title=SundanceTV Partners With BBC One for Abi Morgan's 'The Split'|date=13 January 2017|work=Variety|first=Oriana|last=Schwindt}}</ref> Series 1 was released on DVD on 4 June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.amazon.co.uk/The-Split-DVD/dp/B07C5P8Q2S |title= The Split|date= 4 June 2018 |via= Amazon }}</ref>\n\nA  second series was commissioned in May 2018 <ref>[https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/967120/The-Split-series-2-BBC-air-date-cast-trailer-plot-Nicola-Walker-renewed-confirmed The Split series 2 BBC air date, cast, trailer, plot] by Emma Nolan,  May 30, 2018</ref> with production beginning in March 2019<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/the-split-s2|title=BBC - Second series of Abi Morgan\u2019s original BBC One drama The Split begins production - Media Centre|website=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> Series 2 sees the return of the Defoe family at newly merged law firm Noble Hale Defoe, with most of the original cast confirmed.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/>  [[Donna Air]] and [[Ben Bailey Smith]]  have been announced as joining the cast for the second series as high profile clients for the law firm<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-03-21/the-split-series-2-donna-air-joins-cast-filming-begins/|title=Donna Air lands role in The Split as second series goes into production|website=Radio Times}}</ref> and [[Damien Molony]] as the character Tyler Donaghue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://damienmolony.org/2019/07/11/new-tv-role-exclusive-damien-molony-joins-bbc-one-legal-drama-the-split-series-2/|title=NEW TV ROLE EXCLUSIVE: Damien Molony joins BBC One legal drama \u2018The Split\u2019|date=11 July 2019}}</ref> The first episode of series 2 aired on BBC One on 11 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvwise.co.uk/2020/01/bbc-one-sets-premiere-date-for-the-split-for-season-2/|title=BBC One Sets Premiere Date For 'The Split' For Season 2|date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{See also|List of The Split characters}}\n===Main cast===\n* [[Nicola Walker]] as [[List of The Split characters#Hannah Stern|Hannah Stern]], a divorce lawyer working for Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Stephen Mangan]] as [[List of The Split characters#Nathan Stern|Nathan Stern]], Hannah's husband, a [[barrister]]<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Fiona Button]] as [[List of The Split characters#Rose Defoe|Rose Defoe]], Hannah's youngest sister.<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Annabel Scholey]] as [[List of The Split characters#Nina Defoe|Nina Defoe]], Hannah's younger sister, a fellow divorce lawyer for Defoe's, the family practice<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Barry Atsma]] as [[List of The Split characters#Christie Carmichael|Christie Carmichael]], Hannah's former boyfriend who also works for Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Stephen Tompkinson]] as [[List of The Split characters#Davey McKenzie|Davey McKenzie]], a millionaire divorcing his wife (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Meera Syal]] as [[List of The Split characters#Goldie McKenzie|Goldie McKenzie]], Davey's wife and his company's secretary (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Anthony Head]] as [[List of The Split characters#Oscar Defoe|Oscar Defoe]], Hannah's long lost father (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Deborah Findlay]] as [[List of The Split characters#Ruth Defoe|Ruth Defoe]], Hannah's mother, the director of the family firm<ref name=deadline1/> \n* [[Rudi Dharmalingam]] as [[List of The Split characters#James Cutler|James Cutler]], Rose\u2019s [[fianc\u00e9]], later husband<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Donna Air]] as [[List of The Split characters#Fi Hansen|Fi Hansen]], a famous presenter divorcing her husband (Series 2)<ref name=inews>{{cite web |url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/television/the-split-season-2-cast-nicola-walker-new-series-episodes-bbc-one-when-start-time-1387255 |title=The Split season 2 cast: who stars with Nicola Walker in the new series, and when it starts on BBC One tonight |last=Selby |first=Jenn |date=11 February 2020 |website=i News |publisher= |access-date=22 February 2020 |quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Bailey Smith]] as [[List of The Split characters#Richie Hansen|Richie Hansen]], Fi's husband (Series 2)<ref name=\"inews\"/>\n\n===Supporting cast===\n* [[Chukwudi Iwuji]] as [[List of The Split characters#Zander Hale|Alexander 'Zander' Hale]], director of Noble & Hale <ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Kobna Holdbrook-Smith]] as [[List of The Split characters#Glen Peters|Glen Peters]], the [[vicar (Anglicanism)|vicar]] performing Rose and James' wedding ceremony (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Maggie O'Neill]] as [[List of The Split characters#Yvonne Duchy|Yvonne Duchy]], Goldie's best friend, who is having an affair with her husband (Series 1)<ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Josette Simon]] as [[List of The Split characters#Maya|Maya]], Oscar Defoe's second partner (Series 1)\n* [[Mathew Baynton]] as [[List of The Split characters#Rex Pope|Rex Pope]], a stand-up comedian <ref name=deadline1/>\n* [[Damien Molony]] as [[List of The Split characters#Tyler Donaghue|Tyler Donaghue]], Zander's fianc\u00e9 (Series 2)\n* Elizabeth Roberts as [[List of The Split characters#Liv Stern|Liv Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's elder daughter<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Mollie Cowen as [[List of The Split characters#Tilly Stern|Tilly Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's younger daughter<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Toby Oliver as [[List of The Split characters#Vinnie Stern|Vinnie Stern]], Hannah and Nathan's son<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Ellora Torchia as [[List of The Split characters#Maggie Lavelle|Maggie Lavelle]], a paralegal at Noble & Hale<ref name=deadline1/>\n* Brenock O'Connor as [[List of The Split characters#Sasha|Sasha]], Liv Stern's boyfriend (Series 1)\n* [[Ian McElhinney]] as [[List of The Split characters#Sasha|Prof Ronnie]], a friend of Hannah Stern's mother (Series 2) \n* [[Chanel Cresswell]] as Kelsey Ashworth (Series 1, episode 2)\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| color1     = #B0C4DE\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1  = 6\n| start1     = {{Start date|2018|4|24|df=y}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2018|5|29|df=y}}\n\n| color2     = #000000\n| link2      = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2  = 6\n| start2     = {{Start date|2020|2|11|df=y}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2020|3|17|df=y}}\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |background=#B0C4DE |overall=6 |series=6 |title=23 |director=20 |writer=20 |airdate=15 |viewers=10 |country=U.K |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=1\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title= Episode 1\n |DirectedBy= Jessica Hobbs\n |WrittenBy= Abi Morgan\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2018|4|24|df=y}}\n |Viewers= 6.89<ref name=\"Barb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-30/|title=Weekly Top 30 Programmes|publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|access-date=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= Hannah represents the ex-wife of top stand-up comedian Rex Pope ([[Mathew Baynton]]) who has engaged in a legal battle to try to prevent him from using material referencing her in his new stand-up arena tour, and also takes on one of her mother's former clients, Davey McKenzie ([[Stephen Tompkinson]]), who has issued divorce proceedings against wife Goldie ([[Meera Syal]]) after more than twenty years of marriage. Hannah's long-lost father, Oscar ([[Anthony Head]]) also returns after a thirty year absence to reclaim his 